&lt;p&gt;This role will be based in one of our Brex offices — San Francisco, New York, or Salt Lake City.&amp;nbsp;We are a hybrid environment that combines the energy and connections of being in the office with the benefits and flexibility of working from home. We currently require a minimum of two coordinated days in the office per week, Wednesday and Thursday. Starting February 2, 2026, we will require three days per week in office - Monday, Wednesday and Thursday. As a perk, we also have up to four weeks per year of fully remote work!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead all aspects of tax at Brex, including planning, strategy, financial reporting, and compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare or manage the preparation of all domestic and foreign tax and information returns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successfully navigate tax audits and examinations by all relevant authorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all tax accounts, including provisions, are properly reflected in relevant financial reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and improve tax systems, processes, and policies across the Company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the oversight of and partnership with external tax advisors as they provide coverage for our local and international operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Finance, People, Sales, Engineering, and other functions as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Payroll and Equity functions in resolving employee-related tax issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare journal entries and perform reconciliations over tax-related accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all tax liabilities and obligations are met in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ad-hoc projects, such as tax credits and incentive planning, as necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of public accounting or private industry experience covering domestic and international operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to both manage a team and operate as an individual contributor to fulfill responsibilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Talented and highly motivated with a self-starter mentality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal skills and ability to manage deadlines effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical, problem-solving solving and decision-making skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective verbal, listening, and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPA License&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Microsoft Office skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Credit card, payment processing, financial services and SaaS industry experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge and experience using NetSuite, Donnelly, Coupa, Looker and/or other data visualization software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The expected salary range for this role is $235,040 - $279,110.&amp;nbsp; However, the starting base pay will depend on a number of factors including the candidate’s location, skills, experience, market demands, and internal pay parity. Depending on the position offered, equity and other forms of compensation may be provided as part of a total compensation package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please be aware, job-seekers may be at risk of targeting by malicious actors looking for personal data. Brex recruiters will only reach out via LinkedIn or email with a&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link&quot; href=&quot;http://brex.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;http://brex.com&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;brex.com&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;domain. Any outreach claiming to be from Brex via other sources should be ignored.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
